78. "The superior man honors virtue and detests the lack of virtue."
79. "The superior man holds righteousness to be of highest importance."
80. "The superior man takes care of his health and cultivates his mind."
81. "The superior man controls himself before he corrects others."
82. "The superior man is humble in his heart and respectful in his behavior."
83. "The superior man is peaceful and easy; the inferior man is always worried."
84. "The superior man is serious but not severe; the inferior man is severe but not serious."
85. "The superior man is quiet and calm, waiting for the appointments of Heaven."
86. "The superior man respects others and is respected by them."
87. "The superior man is straightforward, yet gentle."
88. "The superior man is just in his conduct and does not forget what is right."
89. "The superior man is happy and contented; the inferior man is always discontented."
90. "The superior man is strict with himself, and patient with others."
91. "The superior man is generous but not wasteful."
92. "The superior man is charitable, but not extravagant."
93. "The superior man is cautious in speech but quick in action."
94. "The superior man is peaceful, and does not engage in disputes."
95. "The superior man does not crave for more than he needs."
96. "The superior man is contented with his position."
97. "The superior man does not act contrary to virtue, even for the space of a single meal."
98. "The superior man is resolute but not unyielding."
99. "The superior man is modest in his desires and avoids excessive indulgence."
100. "The superior man is attentive to his thoughts, and keeps them free from evil."

